> A meal you can make all on a single baking sheet? Sign us up! Tonight's pan is filled with shawarma-spiced chicken, crispy-spiced potato wedges, and roasted zucchini and onion. Add to that a lemony feta crema—on the side for dipping—and dinner is ready to serve.

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @Turkish Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

In a #large bowl{}, combine garlic, @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, a large drizzle of oil, juice from half the lemon, salt, and pepper.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; add to bowl and turn to coat. Set aside to marinate.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss zucchini and onion with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully add veggies and chicken to empty side. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add veggies and chicken to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until potatoes and veggies are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @feta cheese{½%cup} in a #small bowl{}; mash with a #spoon{}. Stir in @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, lemon zest, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Divide chicken, veggies, and potato wedges between plates. Serve with lemon feta crema for drizzling or dipping, and remaining lemon wedges on the side.